In a medium saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat and add mushrooms. Saute mushrooms until tender, approximately 5 minutes. Remove pan from heat and add flour. Whisk to blend, forming a paste. Return pan to heat and cook 1 minute. Gradually add water and LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk to mushroom-and-flour mixture, blending well after each addition. Add remaining ingredients. Stir constantly; heat to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 2 minutes. Adjust seasonings to taste.